# Steering — Repo conventions

## Branch naming

- `feat/<short-desc>` — new features
- `fix/<short-desc>` — bug fixes
- `refactor/<short-desc>` — refactors
- `parallel-dev/<feature_id>/<task_id>` — parallel-dev worker branches (RESERVED — don't manually use)
- `merge/<feature_id>` — merge-coordinator branches (RESERVED — don't manually use)
- `snapshot/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<purpose>` — rollback snapshots

## Commit messages

- First line: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>` (max 70 chars)
- type ∈ {feat, fix, refactor, test, docs, chore, perf, build, ci}
- Body wraps at 72 chars, explains WHY not WHAT
- Workers' commits get auto-added `Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>`

## MR conventions

- Title matches commit-message first-line format
- Description includes: Summary / Test plan / Rollback notes
- High-risk MRs auto-flag `[NEEDS-HUMAN]` per `classify-feature-risk.py`
- 1 MR per feature (workers don't open MRs)

## File layout

- `src/<module>/...` — production code
- `tests/<module>/...` — tests (mirrors src layout)
- `contracts/` — OpenAPI / AsyncAPI / JSON Schemas
- `adr/` — Architecture Decision Records
- `spec/<NNN-feature>/` — per-feature specs
- `steering/` — cross-cutting rules (this dir)
- `docs/runbooks/` — operator runbooks
